        "Fatha: A small diagonal line written above a letter ( َ ). This sign is called Fatha in Arabic. It gives the letter a short \"a\" sound.",
        "For example, when Fatha is added to the letter Sin (س), it is read as sa (سَ); when it is added to the letter Sad (ص), it is also read as sa (صَ), with a deeper pronunciation."
